  "title": "Engineering Assistant (Semiconductor, 12-hr shift)",
  "description": "<p><em>We are looking for an </em><em><strong>entry-level Engineering Assistant</strong></em><em> to support production operations and ensure high product quality and yield. The role involves monitoring key process parameters, analysing performance data, and working with different teams to maintain smooth operations.</em></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Monitor critical production parameters to maintain product quality and yield.</li>\n  <li>Analyse daily production performance and implement preventive or corrective actions for any deviations.</li>\n  <li>Prepare in-process yield reports and perform loss analysis.</li>\n  <li>Review and handle disposition of materials for final products.</li>\n  <li>Detect and report abnormal losses or defects in a timely manner.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with various departments to ensure seamless production processes.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Engineering or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>Strong attention to detail and problem-solving skills.</li>\n  <li>Good teamwork and communication abilities.</li>\n  <li>Able to work <strong>12-hour shifts.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R1326740</p>",
